644
00:34:01,215 --> 00:34:02,590
but it means that
you can lose up

645
00:34:02,590 --> 00:34:05,710
to all of your energy
in one single collision.

646
00:34:05,710 --> 00:34:08,800
And this is what makes
hydrogen such a good moderator

647
00:34:08,800 --> 00:34:11,770
or a slower down of neutrons,
is when it undergoes

648
00:34:11,770 --> 00:34:15,820
elastic scattering, especially
at energies below an MeV or so,

649
00:34:15,820 --> 00:34:18,790
which is where most of the
neutrons in the reactor are,

650
00:34:18,790 --> 00:34:20,050
it just bounces around.

651
00:34:20,050 --> 00:34:22,030
And the more it hits
hydrogens, the more

652
00:34:22,030 --> 00:34:25,222
